  1→//axhob_operation
  2→{rbtgo_depot_initialize}
  3→
  4→The
  5→{at_operator}
  6→completes one-time depot initialization after
  7→{rbtgo_depot_create}
  8→has provisioned infrastructure.
  9→This procedure validates the
 10→{rbra_rubric_repo_url}
 11→for {rbtgr_rubric_repo} management and completes the GitHub OAuth authorization for the
 12→{rbtgi_source_connection}
 13→created by
 14→{rbtgo_depot_create}
 15→in PENDING state.
 16→
 17→This procedure is idempotent — safe to re-run.
 18→Steps already complete (URL already valid, connection already COMPLETE) are skipped.
 19→
 20→//axhoq_precondition
 21→[[rbtgo_depot_initialize_depot_exists]]
 22→{rbtgo_depot_initialize_depot_exists}
 23→* {rbtgi_depot}
 24→exists (completed
 25→{rbtgo_depot_create})
 26→
 27→//axhoq_precondition
 28→[[rbtgo_depot_initialize_governor_exists]]
 29→{rbtgo_depot_initialize_governor_exists}
 30→* {rbtr_governor}
 31→created for this depot (completed
 32→{rbtgo_governor_reset})
 33→
 34→//axhoq_precondition
 35→[[rbtgo_depot_initialize_gdc_configured]]
 36→{rbtgo_depot_initialize_gdc_configured}
 37→* {rbrr_gdc_connection_name} and {rbrr_gdc_region} configured in RBRR
 38→
 39→//axhoq_precondition
 40→[[rbtgo_depot_initialize_rubric_url_configured]]
 41→{rbtgo_depot_initialize_rubric_url_configured}
 42→* {rbrr_governor_rbra_file} contains {rbra_rubric_repo_url}
 43→
 44→//axhoq_precondition
 45→[[rbtgo_depot_initialize_operator_browser]]
 46→{rbtgo_depot_initialize_operator_browser}
 47→* Operator has browser access for GitHub OAuth authorization
 48→
 49→//axhos_step
 50→[[rbtgo_depot_initialize_authenticate]]
 51→{rbtgo_depot_initialize_authenticate}
 52→. *Authenticate as
 53→{rbtr_director}*:
 54→.. Execute
 55→{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
 56→
 57→//axhos_step
 58→[[rbtgo_depot_initialize_load_rubric_url]]
 59→{rbtgo_depot_initialize_load_rubric_url}
 60→. *Load Rubric Repo URL*:
 61→.. {rbbc_call}
 62→{rbtoe_rbra_load}
 63→for
 64→{rbrr_director_rbra_file}
 65→.. {rbbc_store}
 66→`«RUBRIC_REPO_URL»` from {rbra_rubric_repo_url}
 67→.. If `«RUBRIC_REPO_URL»` is empty:
 68→... {rbbc_show}
 69→"RBRA_RUBRIC_REPO_URL is not set in Governor RBRA file"
 70→... {rbbc_show}
 71→guidance for creating a rubric repository: create a repo on a git host (GitHub as reference example), generate a fine-grained PAT with Contents read/write, construct the authenticated URL as `https://x-access-token:<PAT>@<host>/<org>/<repo>.git`, and add `RBRA_RUBRIC_REPO_URL` to the Governor RBRA file
 72→... {rbbc_fatal}
 73→"Set RBRA_RUBRIC_REPO_URL in Governor RBRA file and re-run"
 74→
 75→//axhos_step
 76→[[rbtgo_depot_initialize_validate_rubric_url]]
 77→{rbtgo_depot_initialize_validate_rubric_url}
 78→. *Validate Rubric Repo URL*:
 79→.. {rbbc_call}
 80→`git ls-remote «RUBRIC_REPO_URL» HEAD` to verify reachability and credential validity
 81→.. If `git ls-remote` fails:
 82→... {rbbc_fatal}
 83→"Rubric repo URL is unreachable or credentials are invalid — check RBRA_RUBRIC_REPO_URL and ensure PAT has Contents:write permission"
 84→.. {rbbc_show}
 85→"Rubric repo URL validated"
 86→
 87→//axhos_step
 88→[[rbtgo_depot_initialize_check_devconnect]]
 89→{rbtgo_depot_initialize_check_devconnect}
 90→. *Check Developer Connect Connection Status*:
 91→.. Construct connection path: `projects/{rbrr_depot_project_id}/locations/{rbrr_gdc_region}/connections/{rbrr_gdc_connection_name}`
 92→.. {rbbc_call}
 93→link:https://cloud.google.com/developer-connect/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.connections/get[developerconnect.connections.get] for `«CONNECTION_PATH»`
 94→.. {rbbc_require}
 95→HTTP 200 — connection exists
 96→.. {rbbc_store}
 97→`«CONNECTION_STAGE»` from `.installationState.stage`
 98→.. If `«CONNECTION_STAGE»` is `COMPLETE`:
 99→... {rbbc_show}
100→"Developer Connect connection already active — skipping OAuth step"
101→... Go to
102→{rbtgo_depot_initialize_poll_connection}
103→
104→//axhos_step
105→[[rbtgo_depot_initialize_grant_console]]
106→{rbtgo_depot_initialize_grant_console}
107→. *Grant Operator Console Access for Developer Connect*:
108→.. {rbbc_require}
109→{rbrp_operator_email} is set
110→.. {rbbc_call}
111→link:https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/reference/rest/v3/projects/setIamPolicy[projects.setIamPolicy] for `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
112→.. Add `{rbrp_operator_email}` with `roles/developerconnect.admin`
113→.. {rbbc_show}
114→"Granted operator Developer Connect admin on depot project"
115→
116→//axhos_step
117→[[rbtgo_depot_initialize_guide_oauth]]
118→{rbtgo_depot_initialize_guide_oauth}
119→. *Guide GitHub OAuth Authorization*:
120→.. {rbbc_store}
121→`«ACTION_URI»` from `.installationState.actionUri` of the connection response
122→.. {rbbc_require}
123→`«ACTION_URI»` is present and non-empty
124→.. {rbbc_show}
125→"Developer Connect connection requires GitHub OAuth authorization"
126→.. {rbbc_show}
127→`«ACTION_URI»` for {at_operator} to open in browser
128→.. Guide {at_operator} through the OAuth flow:
129→... GCP Console shows "Request GitHub OAuth token" — click "I understand and continue"
130→... GitHub shows "Install Google Cloud Developer Connect" — select the account/org hosting the {rbtgr_rubric_repo}
131→... Repository access: select "Only select repositories" and pick the {rbtgr_rubric_repo}
132→... Click "Install"
133→... GitHub redirects back to GCP; OAuth token stored in Secret Manager
134→.. Wait for {at_operator} confirmation
135→
136→//axhos_step
137→[[rbtgo_depot_initialize_poll_connection]]
138→{rbtgo_depot_initialize_poll_connection}
139→. *Poll Connection Until Active*:
140→.. {rbbc_poll}
141→link:https://cloud.google.com/developer-connect/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.connections/get[developerconnect.connections.get] for `«CONNECTION_PATH»`
142→.. Extract `.installationState.stage` from each response
143→.. Poll at `RBGC_EVENTUAL_CONSISTENCY_SEC` intervals until stage reaches `COMPLETE` or `RBGC_MAX_CONSISTENCY_SEC` timeout
144→.. {rbbc_require}
145→`installationState.stage` is `COMPLETE`
146→.. {rbbc_fatal}
147→if timeout: "Developer Connect OAuth did not complete — re-open the authorization URI and try again"
148→
149→//axhos_step
150→[[rbtgo_depot_initialize_final_validation]]
151→{rbtgo_depot_initialize_final_validation}
152→. *Final Validation*:
153→.. {rbbc_show}
154→"Running final validation..."
155→.. Verify {rbtgr_rubric_repo} URL: repeat `git ls-remote` call — {rbbc_require} successful exit
156→.. Verify Developer Connect: repeat connections.get call — {rbbc_require} `installationState.stage` is `COMPLETE`
157→.. {rbbc_show}
158→"Depot initialization complete"
159→
160→//axhoo_output
161→[[rbtgo_depot_initialize_validated_url]]
162→{rbtgo_depot_initialize_validated_url}
163→* Validated {rbra_rubric_repo_url} — confirmed reachable via `git ls-remote`
164→
165→//axhoo_output
166→[[rbtgo_depot_initialize_active_connection]]
167→{rbtgo_depot_initialize_active_connection}
168→* Active {rbtgi_source_connection} — `installationState.stage` is `COMPLETE`
169→
170→//axhoo_output
171→[[rbtgo_depot_initialize_oauth_token]]
172→{rbtgo_depot_initialize_oauth_token}
173→* OAuth token automatically stored in Secret Manager (managed by Developer Connect, not by operator)
174→
175→//axhoc_completion
176→Successful execution confirms the depot is fully initialized for
177→{rbtgo_rubric_inscribe}
178→operations.
179→The
180→{rbra_rubric_repo_url}
181→enables {rbtgr_rubric_repo} management and the
182→{rbtgi_source_connection}
183→enables Cloud Build to access the {rbtgr_rubric_repo}.
184→Proceed to
185→{rbtgo_rubric_inscribe}
186→to set up per-vessel build infrastructure.
187→

